As much as I like your video's in terms of quality, comprehensiveness & educational value I would argue that you are reaching a plateau in terms of available technology. If I might suggest something is that you start to diverge from this path and pause on doing yearly iterations of tutorials on the programming languages.

I am certain that you as a content creator can feel like you keep doing the same things over and over again. Not that your content is bad... It's quite the contrary. IMO you're the best tutor on the interwebs by far in terms of enthusiasm, method & all round knowledge while being a down to earth person.

What I mean to say is that programming languages & its combo's into stacks can only get you this far. A man with your talent would be imo the best source for more in-depth programming paradigms & design patterns instead of merely programming languages. If you were to teach the paradigms & design patterns and architecture the viewers would be taught "how & why" to program in a certain way. It could evolve into a tutorial series about a microservice architecture... Especially since you have the knowledge to do so. 

When you have a microservice architecture series you could even pull it a bit further & introduce the microfrontend architecture so you can end up having a loosely coupled architecture, having microservices, communicating through an event aggregator & have the microfrontends communicate between their only contract being native DOM events. You are right person to do so, since nobody is able to teach this the right way.

Mind you that I started my dev/architecture journey by following your videos & uploads. I started HERE & ended up being a Senior Full Stack Developer, growing into frontend/domain architecture  position now.

Just my 2 cents.

Also nothing on progressive web apps, everybody skip that. :)
